    "date": "2017-07-02",
    "comment": "Rationale: Dynorphins are agonists of the kappa-opioid receptors. The pro-peptide, called Proenkephalin-B or Preprodynorphin is cleaved into 9 hormone-like peptides, one of which is Dynorphin A (1-8) (see e.g. PMID: 6316163).\nThe paper presents pre-embedding immunoperoxidase-based electron microscopy analysis and shows that Dynorphin A (1-8) is a presynaptic peptide associates with the rims of small SVs (Figure 4-6, very clear in figure 6b) and with the core of large-dense core vesicles. Experimental description: 'Four adult male Sprague-Dawley rats (Taconic Farms,\nNJ; 200-250 g) were deeply anesthetized with sodium'",
